#Noctuidae
Acronicta aceris (Sycamore)

#Bombycidae
Bombyx mori (Silk moth)

#Sphingidae
Deilephila elpenor (Elephant hawk moth)
Hyles euphorbiae (Spurge hawk moth)
Daphnis nerii (Oleander hawk moth)
Acherontia atropos (Death's-head hawk moth)

#Erebidae
Tyria jacobaeae (Cinnabar moth)
Utetheisa ornatrix (Ornate moth)
Amata phegea (Nine-spotted moth)
Apantesis arge (Arge moth)
Apantesis phalerata (Harnessed tiger moth)
Arctia caja (Garden tiger moth)

#Saturniidae
Automeris io (Peacock moth)
Attacus atlas (Atlas moth)
Saturnia pavonia (Emperor moth)
Actias luna (Luna moth)
Antheraea polyphemus (Polyphemus moth)
Hyalophora cecropia (Cecropia moth)
Samia cynthia (Ailanthus silkmoth)
Eacles imperialis (Imperial moth)
Argema mittrei (Comet moth)
Citheronia regalis (Regal moth)

#Papilionidae (Swallowtail)
Papilio machaon: black-and-yellow, one red and several blue spots on hindwing, northern hemisphere
Papilio nireus: black with blue band and spots, Africa
Papilio ulysses: blue center and wide black edges, Australia
Zerynthia: black-and-yellow with red spots, Mediterranean
Parnassius apollo (Apollo)
Zerynthia polyxena (Southern festoon)
Pachliopta hector (Crimson rose)
Trogonoptera (Birdwing): large, males black with triangular blue/green markings, SE Asia
Troides (Birdwing): large, black forewings, yellow hindwings with black veins, South Asia

#Nymphalidae: brightly colored upper side, dull underwings
Aglais io (European peacock): Eurasia
- wings: orange base, yellow and black spots, bottom margin black with blue spots
- larvae feed on nettle
Aglais urticae (Small tortoiseshell): Eurasia
- wings: red base, blue-yellow eyespot on each wing
- larvae feed on nettle
Vanessa atalanta (Red admiral): northern hemisphere
- wings: black base, red band on each wing, white spots near forewing tips
- larvae feed on nettle
Vanessa cardui (Painted lady)
--
Danaus plexippus (Monarch): America + Oceania, migratory
- caterpillar: 2 tentacle pairs, white-black-yellow stripes
- wings: orange base, black veins, black border with white dots
Danaus gilippus (Queen): America
- caterpillar: 3 tentacle pairs, white-black-yellow stripes
- wings: orange base, black border and white dots
Tirumala (Blue tiger): Africa + south Asia + Australia, migratory
- wings: dark base, light blue spots
--
Argynnis (Fritillary): northern hemisphere
- wings: orange base, black markings
--
Lexias dirtea (Archduke)
Limenitis archippus (Viceroy)
Cethosia cyane (Leopard lacewing)
Precis octavia (Gaudy commodore)
Hamadryas amphinome (Red cracker)
Myscelia cyaniris (Blue wave)
Heliconius charithonia (Zebra longwing)
Heliconius erato (Red postman)
Limenitis camilla (White admiral)
Adelpha (Sister): America
- wings: dark base, wide white band, orange spot near forewing tips

#Pieridae
Pieris brassicae (Large white)
Anthocharis cardamines (Orange tip)
Delias eucharis (Jezebel)

#Lycaenidae
Polyommatus icarus (Common blue)
Curetis bulis (Bright sunbeam)
